                    	<note xml:id="n_dating" type="dating">
                    	    
<p xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">Letter headed: ‘Jully 22’. It is clear from the subjects discussed that this was Sunday, 22 July 1888.</p>
                    	</note>
                    
                    
                    
                    	<note xml:id="n_remarks" type="remarks">
                    	    
                                    
<p xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">The letter, written in English, has not survived in its entirety; it ends in the middle of a sentence and there is no signature. In <ref target="let650.xml">letter 650</ref> to Theo, Vincent writes about things in the present letter; it emerges that in the missing section Russell must have invited Vincent to go to Belle-Île, and that he very much wanted to paint Vincent’s portrait again.</p>
                                    
                                
                    	</note>
                    
